Onyekachukwu Meluwa, Warri An angry mob has set ablaze an unidentified young man allegedly caught with a locally-made pistol, while attacking a Point of Sale operator in Otovwodo, Ughellli Local Government Area of Delta State. It was gathered that the man lost his life to jungle justice on Tuesday after the mob caught up with him. PUNCH Metro learnt that the victim was set ablaze after his gang of three brandished a gun to dispose the PoS operator, who raised the alarm that attracted the mob. An eyewitness, Agholor Otete, said, “The young man was caught and set ablaze around the popular Shop Fair Mall that is located directly opposite the Otovwodo motor park in Ughelli after his gang of three brandished a gun to dispose a female PoS operator, who quickly raised the alarm that alerted the mob.” When contacted, the state Police Public Relations Officer, Onome Onovwakpoyeya, confirmed the incident. “Yes, it’s true. An armed robber was burnt to death for robbing a lady doing the PoS business on Tuesday,” she stated. Copyright PUNCH.
